  "title": "2025 AMC 12B Problems/Problem 3",
  "problem": "What is the value of $i(i-1)(i-2)(i-3)$ , where $i = \\sqrt{-1}$ ? $\\textbf{(A)}~6-5i \\qquad \\textbf{(B)}~-10i \\qquad \\textbf{(C)}~10i \\qquad \\textbf{(D)}~-10 \\qquad \\textbf{(E)}~10$",
  "solution": "We find that $i(i-3)=-1-3i$ and $(i-1)(i-2)=-1-3i+2=1-3i$ , so\n\\begin{align}\ni(i-1)(i-2)(i-3)&=i(i-3)\\cdot (i-1)(i-2)\\\\\n&=(-1-3i)(1-3i)\\\\\n&=-(1+3i)(1-3i)\\\\\n&=-(1^2-(3i)^2)\\\\\n&=-(1+9)\\\\\n&=\\boxed{\\textbf{(D)}~-10 }\n\\end{align} ~ eevee9406",
